<item>
            <title>[LU-8687] Fix test-framework.sh for ost-pools suite in case of separate MGS/MDS setup</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8687</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This ticket is to make the changes in t-f, for ost-pools suite, when the cluster setup has separate MGS and MDS configured on different nodes.&lt;br/&gt;
The Lustre client needs to be mounted on MGS node for ost-pools suite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;The lctl command MUST be run on the MGS. Another requirement &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; managing OST pools is to either have the MDT and MGS on the same node or have a Lustre client mounted on the MGS node, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; it is separate from the MDS.

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
